			"after": " Teresa Cristina died three weeks after their arrival in Europe 271 272 and Isabel and her family moved to another place while Pedro settled first in Cannes and later in Paris 273 274 Pedro s last couple of years were lonely and melancholic as he lived in modest hotels without money and writing in his journal of dreams in which he was allowed to return to Brazil 275 He never supported a restoration of the monarchy once stating that he had no desire to return to the position which I occupied especially not by means of conspiracy of any sort 276 One day he caught an infection that progressed quickly into pneumonia 277 278 Pedro rapidly declined and died at 00 35 on 5 December 1891 surrounded by his family 279 His last words were May God grant me these last wishes peace and prosperity for Brazil 280 While the body was being prepared a sealed package in the room was found and next to it a message written by the Emperor himself It is soil from my country I wish it to be placed in my coffin in case I die away from my fatherland 281 ",
